originalText.text: Warm and friendly office. Dr Jennifer Reyes is meticulous to detail and her  professionalism is most apparent . As a patient and a physician I genuinely trust her judgment. She is thoughtful in her approach and not reactive- I’ve had some tough stuff to deal with and have been most impressed by her clinical approach.

originalText.text: Went via a recommendation and was extremely pleased with my cleaning! Everyone was so kind and helpful. A lovely environment to put one at ease. And they have the cutest little helper to greet you!

originalText.text: Going to the dentist always caused me anxiety. I think I had so many cavities as a kid, that I was traumatized by the fillings and the fear of my youth.  I've been to a number of dentists in my life, some better than others, but I have to say that after all my experiences, finding Dr. Reyes has been a safe haven for me. She has restored my hope that I can get through any procedure anytime.  Dr. Reyes listens to your needs, she is gentle at her work, tells you what to expect when she's doing her work, she is very patient and makes you feel like you've known each other before.  Her work is impeccable.  I needed a crown replaced and I have to say she is the Queen, not me.  I am so at ease visiting Dr. Reyes' office that I'm motivated to do more work on old fillings, etc.  I highly recommend Dr. Reyes to all, but especially to those in the dentist panic group.  You won't be disappointed. You will walk out smiling and proud you got through it.

originalText.text: Dr. Reyes was awesome. I have a lot of anxiety about going to the dentist but she was very gentle and put me at ease. She even provided me with numbing gel for sensitive areas. I have minimal residual soreness after the dentist like prior experiences. She will definitely be my go-to dentist moving forward!

originalText.text: Dr. Reyes is a fantastic dentist. She is extremely careful and sensitive to her patients’ needs. And her skill and professionalism are top-notch. One time, after she’d adjusted a crown until it seemed perfect to me, she told me she wanted to redo it. One part was a little thin. It would probably be just fine, she said, but she didn’t want to risk that I’d chomp down on a bone or a hard candy and have it crack. (As it happens, I know someone who had a different dentist’s crown crack because it was too thin somewhere!) That is typical of Dr. Reyes. She tries to anticipate and prevent problems. Like most people, I have never much liked going to the dentist—but actually look forward to my visits with Dr. Reyes.
